#Checking multiple conditions

#Python allows you to check multiple conditions, using the keyword "and" you can check if both conditions are true.
#It's simple, if both are true then its true if both are false then its false. And if only one of them is false and the other is true it is still false.

age_0 = 22
age_1 = 18
age_0 >= 21 and age_1 >= 21

#Here age_0 is true but age_1 is false because 18 is not greater than or equal to 21. Therefore this is FALSE

age_1 = 22

age_0 >= 21 and age_1 >= 21 #Here I changed age_1 to 22 which is greater than 21 and that means both tests are true and therefore it is TRUE
#If you want to improve readability, you can add parenthesis to the tests

#You can use parenthesis to improve readability but its not required, and it would come out with the parenthesis as well. 

#Here is how we can check multiple conditions. Here is the or expression, the or expression will turn out FALSE if both are false.

age_0 = 22 
